1
00:00:01,394 --> 00:00:05,029
There are many possibilities,

2
00:00:05,029 --> 00:00:10,214
but at all cost we want 
to avoid thinking offensively

3
00:00:10,214 --> 00:00:14,642
about Vaiṣṇavas
of the least adhikār;

4
00:00:14,642 --> 00:00:17,733
what to speak of
to the highest position.

5
00:00:19,852 --> 00:00:22,830
Because in the case
of the highest position

6
00:00:22,846 --> 00:00:25,267
that’s suicidal.

7
00:00:25,612 --> 00:00:28,361
[Progressive Vision]

8
00:00:28,708 --> 00:00:30,393
But Śrīla Guru Mahārāj,

9
00:00:30,393 --> 00:00:33,221
he would remind us,
he said,

10
00:00:33,221 --> 00:00:37,429
“Even a new person 
we should show respect to,”

11
00:00:38,103 --> 00:00:41,135
he said, “because first of all
now they’re connected

12
00:00:41,135 --> 00:00:44,555
to what we say 
is the highest thing,

13
00:00:44,555 --> 00:00:47,906
and the most wonderful thing,
and the most divine thing.

14
00:00:47,906 --> 00:00:50,228
Now they’re connected to it.

15
00:00:50,228 --> 00:00:53,342
They’re appreciating it,
they have their connection.

16
00:00:53,342 --> 00:00:56,433
And”, he added,
he said,

17
00:00:56,433 --> 00:00:59,335
“God willing,
I may be going slowly,

18
00:00:59,335 --> 00:01:01,725
and they’re going 
very rapidly.

19
00:01:01,725 --> 00:01:07,566
So it’s not inconceivable 
that they could surpass me,

20
00:01:07,566 --> 00:01:11,430
and I would be 
in a position in the future

21
00:01:11,430 --> 00:01:14,720
to receive grace
from them.”

22
00:01:16,520 --> 00:01:19,548
Of course,
hearing such an explanation

23
00:01:20,009 --> 00:01:21,320
we’ll understand—

24
00:01:21,320 --> 00:01:24,870
this is the vision 
of a mahā-bhāgavata.

25
00:01:24,870 --> 00:01:28,095
So, who’s the most exalted,
he’s saying,

26
00:01:28,095 --> 00:01:32,216
“Even a new person
we should show respect to.”

27
00:01:33,112 --> 00:01:36,041
That’s Guru Mahārāj’s position.

28
00:01:38,615 --> 00:01:41,856
And just to add to that
he’s repeatedly saying,

29
00:01:41,856 --> 00:01:44,817
“I am a student,
not a finished professor

30
00:01:44,817 --> 00:01:46,777
knowing anything 
and everything.”

31
00:01:46,777 --> 00:01:48,743
He said, 
“The student.”

32
00:01:48,743 --> 00:01:51,564
And that’s the best position
to be in is a student.

33
00:01:51,564 --> 00:01:53,259
Forever a student.
He said, “Why?

34
00:01:53,259 --> 00:01:55,877
Because a student 
can make mistakes,

35
00:01:55,877 --> 00:02:01,314
a student can learn more—
it’s a progressive position.”

36
00:02:01,410 --> 00:02:07,451
Whereas when you’re cornered 
in the ‘finished professor’

37
00:02:07,451 --> 00:02:10,363
knowing anything and everything,
never makes a mistake,

38
00:02:10,363 --> 00:02:12,961
everything they say, do, etc. 
is perfect.

39
00:02:12,961 --> 00:02:15,583
He said,
“That is a static position,

40
00:02:15,583 --> 00:02:17,720
you can only 
go down from there,

41
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:20,670
whereas the student 
can make progress.”

